transcripts.text: Hi Beast Family, it's Brooke.  I'm in Dayton, Ohio after the tornadoes hit.  This is what is left of a shopping plaza.  Everything is completely destroyed.  Rite Aid off of Dixie Drive in Dayton.  Beauty Supply Store on Dixie Drive completely demolished.
It's hot.  Our food's gone.  We just went and probably spent about $400 or $500 in food.

So... power lines, everything, everywhere.  You can't even drive through.  You can't even walk through.  It's pretty much a jungle you have to navigate through on Dixie Drive in order to dodge debris and trees, limbs, power lines, just to walk down the sidewalk.
